    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237121> ;
    dc:creator "Dronen, Norman O.; Blend, Charles K." ;
    dc:title "Cyclocoelum oculeus Kossack 1911" ;
    trt:augmentsTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Cyclocoelum_oculeus_Kossack_1911> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4053.1.1> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4053.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "100" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "4053" ;
    dc:creator "Dronen, Norman O.; Blend, Charles K." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Updated keys to the genera in the subfamilies of Cyclocoelidae Stossich, 1902, including a reconsideration of species assignments, species keys and the proposal of a new genus in Szidatitreminae Dronen, 2007" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237121> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237121>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14 – 18. Diagrammatic representations of species representing the genera assigned to Ophthalmophaginae Harrah, 1922. 14. Ophthalmophagus Stossich 1902 represented by Ophthalmophagus bucephali Dronen & Blend, 2007, adapted from Dronen & Blend (2007); 15. Bothrigaster Dollfus, 1948 represented by Bothrigaster variolaris (Fuhrmann, 1904) adapted from Fuhrmann (1904); 16. Spaniometra Kossack, 1911 represented by Spaniometra oculobia (Cohn, 1902), adapted from Cohn (1902); 17. Porphyriotrema Duggal & Toor, 1985 represented by Porphyriotrema indica Duggal & Toor, 1985, adapted from Duggal & Toor (1985); 18. Promptenovum Witenberg, 1923 represented by Promptenovum vanbenedeni Witenberg, 1923 (= Monostomum mutabile Zeder of van Beneden 1858), adapted from van Beneden (1858) and Kanev et al. (2002 a). Abbreviations: A, ventral sucker; C, cecum; G, genital pore; O, ovary; P, pharynx; T, testis; U, uterus; V, vitelline field." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/237121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

